    <description>Stems prostrate, decumbent, or ascending to erect, simple or branched, 0.5–4 dm,
        somewhat succulent, glaucous, glabrous; rhizomes slender, bulblets absent, leafy to apex.
        Leaves opposite proximally, becoming alternate and crowded distally; petiole absent; blade
        narrowly lanceolate, elliptic, or ovate, 0.2–2.6 × 0.1–6(–12) cm, base rounded to slightly
        cuneate or sometimes truncate, margins entire, plane, apex obtuse to rounded (or acute),
        surfaces glabrous; venation single-veined. Inflorescences axillary, solitary flowers.
        Pedicels absent. Flowers: sepals 5, calyx not streaked, 3–5 mm, stipitate-glandular, lobes
        ovate, somewhat succulent throughout; petals absent; filaments distinct, equaling to
        slightly longer than calyx; staminodes absent. Capsules 2.5–3.5 mm, not punctate, glabrous.
        2n = 30, 60.</description>
    <phenology>Flowering spring–summer</phenology>
    <habitat> Moist, alkaline or saline areas, coastal tideflats, inland meadows, stream
