    <discussion>There is a late nineteenth century record of Lysimachia maritima from Monmouth
        County, New Jersey. No specimens have been found to substantiate reports
        (http://www.natureserve.org) of the species occurring in Nunavut.</discussion>
    <discussion>Infraspecific taxa have been proposed based on habit, leaf shape, and capsule size.
